{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "web:matthew.15",
    "translationId": "web",
    "bookSlug": "matthew",
    "chapterNumber": 15,
    "referenceLabel": "Matthew 15",
    "summary": "Source text for Matthew 15 in World English Bible."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "web:matthew.15.1",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "matthew",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Matthew 15:1",
      "text": "Then Pharisees and scribes came to Jesus from Jerusalem, saying,",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "web:matthew.15.2",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "matthew",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Matthew 15:2",
      "text": "“Why do your disciples disobey the tradition of the elders? For they don’t wash their hands when they eat bread.”",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:matthew.15.3",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "matthew",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Matthew 15:3",
      "text": "He answered them, “Why do you also disobey the commandment of God because of your tradition?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:matthew.15.4",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "matthew",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Matthew 15:4",
      "text": "For God commanded, ‘Honor your father and your mother,’ and, ‘He who speaks evil of father or mother, let him be put to death.’",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:matthew.15.5",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "matthew",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Matthew 15:5",
      "text": "But you say, ‘Whoever may tell his father or his mother, “Whatever help you might otherwise have gotten from me is a gift devoted to God,”",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:matthew.15.6",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "matthew",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Matthew 15:6",
      "text": "he shall not honor his father or mother.’ You have made the commandment of God void because of your tradition.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:matthew.15.7",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "matthew",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Matthew 15:7",
      "text": "You hypocrites! Well did Isaiah prophesy of you, saying,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:matthew.15.8",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "matthew",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Matthew 15:8",
      "text": "‘These people draw near to me with their mouth, and honor me with their lips; but their heart is far from me.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:matthew.15.9",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "matthew",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Matthew 15:9",
      "text": "And they worship me in vain, teaching as doctrine rules made by men.’”",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:matthew.15.10",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "matthew",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Matthew 15:10",
      "text": "He summoned the multitude, and said to them, “Hear, and understand.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:matthew.15.11",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "matthew",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Matthew 15:11",
      "text": "That which enters into the mouth doesn’t defile the man; but that which proceeds out of the mouth, this defiles the man.”",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:matthew.15.12",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "matthew",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Matthew 15:12",
      "text": "Then the disciples came and said to him, “Do you know that the Pharisees were offended when they heard this saying?”",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:matthew.15.13",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "matthew",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Matthew 15:13",
      "text": "But he answered, “Every plant which my heavenly Father didn’t plant will be uprooted.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:matthew.15.14",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "matthew",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Matthew 15:14",
      "text": "Leave them alone. They are blind guides of the blind. If the blind guide the blind, both will fall into a pit.”",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:matthew.15.15",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "matthew",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "Matthew 15:15",
      "text": "Peter answered him, “Explain the parable to us.”",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:matthew.15.16",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "matthew",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "Matthew 15:16",
      "text": "So Jesus said, “Do you also still not understand?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:matthew.15.17",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "matthew",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "Matthew 15:17",
      "text": "Don’t you understand that whatever goes into the mouth passes into the belly and then out of the body?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:matthew.15.18",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "matthew",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "Matthew 15:18",
      "text": "But the things which proceed out of the mouth come out of the heart, and they defile the man.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:matthew.15.19",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "matthew",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "Matthew 15:19",
      "text": "For out of the heart come evil thoughts, murders, adulteries, sexual sins, thefts, false testimony, and blasphemies.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:matthew.15.20",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "matthew",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "Matthew 15:20",
      "text": "These are the things which defile the man; but to eat with unwashed hands doesn’t defile the man.”",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:matthew.15.21",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "matthew",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 21,
      "referenceLabel": "Matthew 15:21",
      "text": "Jesus went out from there and withdrew into the region of Tyre and Sidon.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:matthew.15.22",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "matthew",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 22,
      "referenceLabel": "Matthew 15:22",
      "text": "Behold, a Canaanite woman came out from those borders and cried, saying, “Have mercy on me, Lord, you son of David! My daughter is severely possessed by a demon!”",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:matthew.15.23",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "matthew",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 23,
      "referenceLabel": "Matthew 15:23",
      "text": "But he answered her not a word. His disciples came and begged him, saying, “Send her away; for she cries after us.”",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:matthew.15.24",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "matthew",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 24,
      "referenceLabel": "Matthew 15:24",
      "text": "But he answered, “I wasn’t sent to anyone but the lost sheep of the house of Israel.”",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:matthew.15.25",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "matthew",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 25,
      "referenceLabel": "Matthew 15:25",
      "text": "But she came and worshiped him, saying, “Lord, help me.”",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:matthew.15.26",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "matthew",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 26,
      "referenceLabel": "Matthew 15:26",
      "text": "But he answered, “It is not appropriate to take the children’s bread and throw it to the dogs.”",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:matthew.15.27",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "matthew",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 27,
      "referenceLabel": "Matthew 15:27",
      "text": "But she said, “Yes, Lord, but even the dogs eat the crumbs which fall from their masters ’ table.”",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:matthew.15.28",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "matthew",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 28,
      "referenceLabel": "Matthew 15:28",
      "text": "Then Jesus answered her, “Woman, great is your faith! Be it done to you even as you desire.” And her daughter was healed from that hour.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:matthew.15.29",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "matthew",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 29,
      "referenceLabel": "Matthew 15:29",
      "text": "Jesus departed from there and came near to the sea of Galilee; and he went up on the mountain and sat there.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:matthew.15.30",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "matthew",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 30,
      "referenceLabel": "Matthew 15:30",
      "text": "Great multitudes came to him, having with them the lame, blind, mute, maimed, and many others, and they put them down at his feet. He healed them,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:matthew.15.31",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "matthew",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 31,
      "referenceLabel": "Matthew 15:31",
      "text": "so that the multitude wondered when they saw the mute speaking, the injured healed, the lame walking, and the blind seeing— and they glorified the God of Israel.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:matthew.15.32",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "matthew",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 32,
      "referenceLabel": "Matthew 15:32",
      "text": "Jesus summoned his disciples and said, “I have compassion on the multitude, because they have continued with me now three days and have nothing to eat. I don’t want to send them away fasting, or they might faint on the way.”",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:matthew.15.33",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "matthew",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 33,
      "referenceLabel": "Matthew 15:33",
      "text": "The disciples said to him, “Where could we get so many loaves in a deserted place as to satisfy so great a multitude?”",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:matthew.15.34",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "matthew",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 34,
      "referenceLabel": "Matthew 15:34",
      "text": "Jesus said to them, “How many loaves do you have?” They said, “Seven, and a few small fish.”",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:matthew.15.35",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "matthew",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 35,
      "referenceLabel": "Matthew 15:35",
      "text": "He commanded the multitude to sit down on the ground;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:matthew.15.36",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "matthew",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 36,
      "referenceLabel": "Matthew 15:36",
      "text": "and he took the seven loaves and the fish. He gave thanks and broke them, and gave to the disciples, and the disciples to the multitudes.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:matthew.15.37",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "matthew",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 37,
      "referenceLabel": "Matthew 15:37",
      "text": "They all ate and were filled. They took up seven baskets full of the broken pieces that were left over.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:matthew.15.38",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "matthew",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 38,
      "referenceLabel": "Matthew 15:38",
      "text": "Those who ate were four thousand men, in addition to women and children.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:matthew.15.39",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "matthew",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 39,
      "referenceLabel": "Matthew 15:39",
      "text": "Then he sent away the multitudes, got into the boat, and came into the borders of Magdala.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
